It took a few goes before I properly got the hang of things (eg. initially I didn't realise that the background/location of the object didn't matter - ie. for "a tomato in a pizza", I thought that a picture of a tomato slice would be a "N" because it didn't show a pizza).

After I got the hang of things, my strategy was: I mentally extracted the key noun (eg. tomato) (i.e. I left it in written form). When the picture was shown on the next page, I immediately analysed the picture to identify what noun it showed and compared this noun to the noun I had extracted from the sentence.
